<p>Keyword optimization is not about hitting a density number or stuffing terms into every HTML element. It is about placing the right keywords in the right places, matching search intent, and building topical depth around every page you publish.</p>
<p>Apply the 1+5 rule. Follow the placement checklist. Audit your existing content every 6 months. That cycle, repeated consistently across every page, is how keyword optimization compounds into rankings.</p>
